Installation steps
------------------
1 - Unzip all the files on your computer, and upload them to your server.
2 - The /temp directory should be chmodded to 777 (you can use www.net2ftp.com to do this).
3 - Set your settings in the settings.php file: 
       - set the root directory of the application
       - activate or deactivate logging
       - allow users to connect to all FTP servers, or only to a specified list
       - ban users and FTP sites
4 - Protect the /temp and the /admin directories. To do this, create .htaccess and .htpasswd files.
5 - A database is only required if you want to log the actions of the users. To create the
    tables, execute the SQL queries in the "create_tables.txt" file. This can be done easily
    in PhpMyAdmin -- the popular front-end to MySQL.
6 - In your php.ini file, register_globals has to be set to "on". If you are
    using a recent PHP version (more recent than 4.0.6) then this is set to
    "off" by default. 
    Note: in some pages, you can already see "PHP 4.0.6 to 4.2.3 upgrade" comments. I am planning the 
    application to work with register_globals set to "off", but this is not finished nor tested.